				<h1 class="page-title">Tag Archives: <span>water harvesting</span></h1>

				




			<div id="post-8134" class="post-8134 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-videos-2 tag-permacutlure tag-water-harvesting">
			<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/two-new-videos-on-permaculture-terrace-creation" title="Permalink to Two New Videos on Permaculture Terrace Creation" rel="bookmark">Two New Videos on Permaculture Terrace Creation</a></h2>

			<div class="entry-meta">
				 <span class="meta-prep meta-prep-author">Posted on</span> <a href="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/two-new-videos-on-permaculture-terrace-creation" title="4:54 pm" rel="bookmark"><span class="entry-date">December 18, 2012</span></a> <span class="byline"><span class="meta-sep">by</span> <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/author/Modern Survival" title="View all posts by Modern Survival">Modern Survival</a></span></span><span class="comments-link"><span class="meta-sep">|</span> <a href="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/two-new-videos-on-permaculture-terrace-creation#comments" title="Comment on Two New Videos on Permaculture Terrace Creation">2 Comments</a></span>
			</div><!-- .entry-meta -->

				<div class="entry-content">
				<div id="tweetbutton8134" class="tw_button" style="float:right;margin-left:10px;"><a href="http://twitter.com/share?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.thesurvivalpodcast.com%2Ftwo-new-videos-on-permaculture-terrace-creation&amp;text=Two%20New%20Videos%20on%20Permaculture%20Terrace%20Creation&amp;related=&amp;lang=en&amp;count=horizontal&amp;counturl=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.thesurvivalpodcast.com%2Ftwo-new-videos-on-permaculture-terrace-creation" class="twitter-share-button"  style="width:55px;height:22px;background:transparent url('http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-tweet-button/tweetn.png') no-repeat  0 0;text-align:left;text-indent:-9999px;display:block;">Tweet</a></div><p>Here are two new videos on building terraces.  These methods will work best in areas with a gentle slope, a source of fill and organic matter on site or at low cost and lots of rocks available.  The basic principles though can be employed anywhere.  These videos are part of a growing series that is now 15 videos long, if you want the <a target="_blank" href="https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLEA7BA330871366B8&amp;feature=view_all" target="_blank">entire play list you can find it here</a>.</p>
