			<div id="post-1662" class="post-1662 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-survival-preparedness tag-frost tag-gardening tag-perennials tag-permaculture tag-water-harvesting tag-winter">
			<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/ten-gardening-steps-for-spring" title="Permalink to Episode-389- Ten Gardening Steps to Get Ready for Spring" rel="bookmark">Episode-389- Ten Gardening Steps to Get Ready for Spring</a></h2>

			<div class="entry-meta">
				 <span class="meta-prep meta-prep-author">Posted on</span> <a href="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/ten-gardening-steps-for-spring" title="10:16 am" rel="bookmark"><span class="entry-date">March 2, 2010</span></a> <span class="byline"><span class="meta-sep">by</span> <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/author/Modern Survival" title="View all posts by Modern Survival">Modern Survival</a></span></span><span class="comments-link"><span class="meta-sep">|</span> <a href="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/ten-gardening-steps-for-spring#comments" title="Comment on Episode-389- Ten Gardening Steps to Get Ready for Spring">5 Comments</a></span>
			</div><!-- .entry-meta -->

				<div class="entry-content">
				<div id="tweetbutton1662" class="tw_button" style="float:right;margin-left:10px;"><a href="http://twitter.com/share?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.thesurvivalpodcast.com%2Ften-gardening-steps-for-spring&amp;text=Episode-389-%20Ten%20Gardening%20Steps%20to%20Get%20Ready%20for%20Spring&amp;related=&amp;lang=en&amp;count=horizontal&amp;counturl=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.thesurvivalpodcast.com%2Ften-gardening-steps-for-spring" class="twitter-share-button"  style="width:55px;height:22px;background:transparent url('http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-tweet-button/tweetn.png') no-repeat  0 0;text-align:left;text-indent:-9999px;display:block;">Tweet</a></div><div class="podPress_content podPress_content_audio_mp3">
<div class="podpress_playerspace podpress_playerspace_audio_mp3 podpress_mp3player" style="display:block;" ><div id="podPressPlayerSpace_2"><!-- podPress --></div></div>
<div class="podPress_downloadlinks podPress_downloadlinks_audio_mp3"><a href="http://www.survivalpodcast.net/audio/2010/3-10/epi-00389-ten-gardening-steps-to-get-ready-for-spring.mp3" target="new" title="Download: Episode-389- Ten Gardening Steps to Get Ready for Spring" class="podpress_downloadimglink podpress_downloadimglink_audio_mp3"><img src="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/wp-content/plugins/podpress/images/audio_mp3_button.png" class="podPress_imgicon podpress_imgicon_audio_mp3" alt="" /></a> <span class="podpress_mediafile_title podpress_mediafile_title_audio_mp3">Episode-389- Ten Gardening Steps to Get Ready for Spring</span> <span class="podpress_mediafile_dursize podpress_mediafile_dursize_audio_mp3">[ 0:01 ]</span> <a href="#podPressPlayerSpace_2" class="podpress_playlink podpress_playlink_audio_mp3" onclick="javascript:podPressShowHidePlayer('2', 'http://www.survivalpodcast.net/audio/2010/3-10/epi-00389-ten-gardening-steps-to-get-ready-for-spring.mp3', 290, 24, 'false', 'http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/wp-content/plugins/podpress//images/vpreview_center.png', 'Episode-389- Ten Gardening Steps to Get Ready for Spring', 'The Survival Podcast'); return false;"><span id="podPressPlayerSpace_2_PlayLink" class="podPress_playerspace_playlink">Play Now</span></a><input type="hidden" id="podPressPlayerSpace_2_OrigURL" value="http://www.survivalpodcast.net/audio/2010/3-10/epi-00389-ten-gardening-steps-to-get-ready-for-spring.mp3" /> | <a href="#podPressPlayerSpace_2" class="podpress_playinpopup podpress_playinpopup_audio_mp3" onclick="javascript:podPressPopupPlayer('2', 'http://www.survivalpodcast.net/audio/2010/3-10/epi-00389-ten-gardening-steps-to-get-ready-for-spring.mp3', 290, 24, 'The Survival Podcast', '1662', 'Episode-389- Ten Gardening Steps to Get Ready for Spring', 'The Survival Podcast'); return false;">Play in Popup</a> | <a href="http://www.survivalpodcast.net/audio/2010/3-10/epi-00389-ten-gardening-steps-to-get-ready-for-spring.mp3" target="new" class="podpress_downloadlink podpress_downloadlink_audio_mp3">Download</a></div></div>
<script type="text/javascript">podPressShowHidePlayer('2', 'http://www.survivalpodcast.net/audio/2010/3-10/epi-00389-ten-gardening-steps-to-get-ready-for-spring.mp3', 290, 24, 'false', 'http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/wp-content/plugins/podpress//images/vpreview_center.png', 'Episode-389- Ten Gardening Steps to Get Ready for Spring', 'The Survival Podcast');</script><p>It is March 2nd and much of the North East just got over &#8220;Snowercane 10&#8243;, heck I am in Texas and I had an inch of snow last week and over 10 inches just two weeks ago.  The northern half of the country has ground that is currently still frozen and I want to talk about gardening?  You bet!  The thaw is coming and odds are many are already behind the power curve.</p>
<p><span style="color: #800000;"><strong>Join me today as we discuss these steps</strong></span></p>
<ul>
<li>Draw a sketch of your property including energy patterns</li>
<li>Pick a few edible perennials to get up and running this year</li>
<li>Estimate and plan for your planting dates</li>
<li>Set up your late frost contingency plans</li>
<li>Go through your potting equipment, clean, sort, organize</li>
<li>Walk your entire property with new eyes</li>
<li>Plan at least one passive water harvesting project for 2010</li>
<li>Plan or begin the development of predator habitat</li>
<li>Identify what is growing now and learn from that</li>
<li>Plan one &#8220;hard scape&#8221; project for 2010</li>
</ul>
<p><span style="color: #800000;"><strong>Additional Resources for Today’s Show</strong></span></p>
