<script type="text/javascript">podPressShowHidePlayer('3', 'http://www.survivalpodcast.net/audio/2010/1-10/epi-00351-an-interview-with-bill-wilson.mp3', 290, 24, 'false', 'http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/wp-content/plugins/podpress//images/vpreview_center.png', 'Episode-351- An Interview with Bill Willson about Permaculutre', 'The Survival Podcast');</script><p>Join me today as I interview Bill Wilson of <a target="_blank" href="http://www.midwestpermaculture.com/" target="_blank">Midwest Permaculture</a> to discuss the concept of Permaculture and the commonalities between the Permaculture and Survivalist communities.  Bill is an amazing guy that followed his dream, walked away from a career and created something special.</p>
<p><span style="color: #800000;"><strong>Join us Today as we Discuss&#8230;</strong></span></p>
<ul>
<li>How Midwest Permaculture came to be</li>
<li>What exactly is Permaculture</li>
<li>The importance of planning in Permaculture vs. agriculture</li>
<li>The training available from Midwest Permaculture</li>
<li>What are some of the long term threats we face</li>
<li>How can Permaculture address and prevent potential threats to our survival</li>
<li>What is a rain garden and how can you build one</li>
<li>How much oil is really left (you have got to hear this one)</li>
<li>Why Permaculture as a solution vs. other options</li>
<li>Who created Permaculture and why it is a true revolution in the traditional sense of the word</li>
<li>How many people can be fed with as little as two acres of well managed land</li>
<li>Why we all should have green houses in temperate climates</li>
</ul>
<p><span style="color: #800000;"><strong>Resources for today’s show…</strong></span></p>
<ul>
